⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Emerald Tablet
node ALC · ALC · ⟦The Emerald Tablet:ALC:599411⟧

WHO   — The Emerald Tablet — as above, so below
WHAT  — The root scripture of the Work, attributed to Hermes Trismegistus: ‘that which is above is as that which is below,’ the doctrine of correspondence.
WHERE — ALC · The Great Work  Framework inputs: Alchemy, catalogued by ROOT0  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because alchemy needed a metaphysics — a claim that metal, cosmos, and soul obey one law — and the Tablet supplied it.
HOW   — As a short, endlessly-glossed text transmitted through Arabic into Latin, translated even by Newton.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  As above, so below — I am the line that made metal, star, and soul a single Work.

